3ˣ=5³, 5ʸ=3⁴
in the first equation, raise both sides to the 1/x power:
(3ˣ)¹/ˣ=(5³)¹/ˣ; 3=5³/ˣ
in the second equation, raise both sides to the 1/4 power:
(5ʸ)¹/⁴=(3⁴)¹/⁴; 5ʸ/⁴=3.  
5³/ˣ=3
5ʸ/⁴=3
Thus:
5³/ˣ=5ʸ/⁴
They have the same base, so the exponents are equal:
3/x=y/4.  Cross multiply:
xy=3⋅4=12

3ˣ=5³, 5ʸ=3⁴
in the first equation, raise both sides to the 1/x power:
(3ˣ)¹/ˣ=(5³)¹/ˣ; 3=5³/ˣ
in the second equation, raise both sides to the 1/4 power:
(5ʸ)¹/⁴=(3⁴)¹/⁴; 5ʸ/⁴=3.  
5³/ˣ=3
5ʸ/⁴=3
Thus:
5³/ˣ=5ʸ/⁴
They have the same base, so the exponents are equal:
3/x=y/4.  Cross multiply:
xy=3⋅4=12
